newsitem.title: INDONESIA: Indonesia late rubber flat despite Tokyo rises.
newsitem.headline: Indonesia late rubber flat despite Tokyo rises.

text.p: Indonesian benchmark SIR20 offer prices were flat in slow late trading on Friday as rises in Tokyo failed to boost local market sentiment, dealers said.

Dealers said SIR20 offer prices for September/October deliveries remained at 55.00-55.50 U.S. cents/lb fob Medan, 54.50-55.00 cents fob Palembang, Surabaya and Padang, and at 53.75-54.24 cents fob Jambi and Pontianak.
"Sentiment remains weak despite rises in Tokyo. There are fresh bids but no deals heard as the bids are considered to be unprofitable for the sellers," one dealer in Jakarta said.
U.S. firms were heard making bids at 54.25-54.50 cents/lb fob Medan for October deliveries, but no deals were heard as sellers were holding firm to their offer prices, another dealer said.
SIR20 was last traded at 54.75 U.S. cents/lb fob Padang for October deliveries and at 55.00 cents/lb fob Medan late on Tuesday, dealers said.
They said high amoniac grade latex was on offer at 2,325-2,350 rupiah/kg in Bandung and Tangerang against the previous 2,425 rupiah/kg. -- Jakarta newsroom +6221 384-6364
